      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented QA procedures for Ansys Mechanical 2023 R1 including version control, regression testing, and change management records.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2023 R1 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented ISO 9001 QA procedures. Solver regression test suite results and release notes reviewed. Version control logs confirm consistent solver version across all simulation runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 suite solved with < 1% deviation from analytical solutions for linear elastic beam bending.",
      "rationale": "Three canonical benchmark problems (Timoshenko beam, thick-walled cylinder, Hertzian contact) solved. Maximum deviation from analytical solution was 0.7%. Code verification criterion satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating < 2% change in QoIs between successive mesh refinements; Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate discretization uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Four-level mesh convergence study performed (element edge lengths 1.0, 0.7, 0.5, 0.35 mm at screw-rod interface). QoI change between finest two meshes: stiffness 0.9%, yield force 1.1%. Richardson extrapolation GCI < 1.5% for all QoIs. Discretization uncertainty included in total simulation uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals < 1e-6 for all load steps; contact penetration < 0.001 mm.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) used for linear steps; Newton-Raphson iteration for nonlinear contact phases. Force residual norm converged to < 5e-7 for all 48 load increments. Maximum contact penetration 0.0004 mm. Numerical solver error deemed negligible relative to other uncertainty sources."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by second analyst; documented simulation plan reviewed prior to execution.",
      "rationale": "Simulation plan reviewed and approved by FDA computational modeler prior to execution. Independent analyst performed blind re-execution of boundary condition setup; no discrepancies identified. Model inputs traceable to CAD drawings and material test certificates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of constitutive model selection (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) supported by material coupon test data and literature.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V coupon tensile tests (n=5 coupons per lot). Elastic modulus 114 GPa, yield strength 880 MPa, tangent modulus 1.1 GPa. Model form uncertainty estimated via sensitivity to tangent modulus ±20%; QoI variation < 3%. Model form judged appropriate for the compression-bending regime of interest."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties derived from lot-specific coupon testing; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of tested constructs; uncertainty propagation documented.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs obtained from coordinate measuring machine (CMM) measurements of the 11 tested constructs (dimensional tolerance ± 0.01 mm). Material inputs from lot-specific tensile coupon tests. Friction coefficient for screw-rod contact assigned as 0.15 ± 0.05 based on tribological literature; sensitivity study confirms QoI variation < 2% across this range. Full input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (n=500 runs)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 constructs tested; dimensional inspection of all samples confirming conformance to design specification.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). All constructs from same production lot; dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to ± 0.05 mm tolerance on all critical dimensions. Sample size sufficient to characterise experimental variability for comparison to simulation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate COU loading environment including load magnitude, rate, and fixture compliance; multiple load conditions evaluated.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 test fixture and protocol followed. Single compression-bending load condition tested (10 mm/min crosshead displacement). Fixture compliance characterised and incorporated into FEA boundary conditions. Achieved level 2 rather than 3 because only one load condition was evaluated; multi-condition testing was not performed. This is the one factor below required level noted in the COU description."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated traceability between experimental and simulation input parameters; any differences quantified and their impact on QoIs assessed.",
      "rationale": "One-to-one mapping established between experimental inputs (fixture geometry, construct dimensions, material lot) and simulation inputs. Minor difference in effective fixture stiffness between labs quantified (Lab B fixture 4% stiffer); sensitivity analysis shows < 1.5% effect on predicted stiffness QoI. Equivalency of inputs judged sufficient for Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric (< 1.96) and percent difference (< 10%) for all three QoIs; uncertainty in both simulation and experimental results accounted for.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement. E/uval values: 1.42, 0.88, 1.31 — all < 1.96. Percent differences: 6.8%, 4.3%, 7.1% — all < 10%. Total simulation uncertainty (uval) includes contributions from discretization, model inputs, and numerical solver. Experimental uncertainty includes inter-laboratory variability. Output comparison criterion satisfied for all QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three quantities specified in ASTM F1717 as primary performance metrics for pedicle screw constructs. These QoIs are directly relevant to the clinical risk of construct loosening and screw fracture. The regulatory submission requires demonstration that FEA predictions of these quantities are credible. QoI relevance is high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on the same device geometry, material, and loading conditions as the COU; any extrapolation from validation to COU is bounded and justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry and Ti-6Al-4V material as the COU device. ASTM F1717 compression-bending protocol directly replicates the mechanical loading scenario of interest. No extrapolation beyond the validated geometry or loading regime is required for the COU. Validation activity relevance is high."
    }
